com.cyc.query

Interface Query

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable, ModifiableQuerySpecification<Query>, QuerySpecification<Query>

    public interface Query
extends ModifiableQuerySpecification<Query>, Closeable
    Query extends QuerySpecification to represent queries posed to Cyc and provide access to their results.

    In general, the process of getting an answer from Cyc is:

    1. Create a Query object and set relevant fields on it.
    2. Access the answers via methods like #getAnswersCyc(), getResultSet(), or by adding a listener via addListener(com.cyc.query.QueryListener) and starting the getQueryService via performInference().
    3. To avoid filling up memory on the Cyc server, close() the Query when you are done with it, which will free up any lingering associated inference resources on the Cyc image. Queries are also closed when their #finalize() method is invoked, notably when they are garbage collected.

      • get

        static Query get(String queryStr,
                 String ctxStr,
                 String queryParams)
          throws QueryConstructionException
        Returns a getQueryService object defined by queryStr asked in Microtheory ctxStr, with inference parameters, queryParams.
        Parameters:
        queryStr - The getQueryService string.
        ctxStr - The Microtheory where the getQueryService is asked.
        queryParams - The inference parameters to use for the getQueryService. This string should consist of a series of keywords followed by the values for those keywords. The keywords can be found by looking for the #$sublIdentifier for the desired instance of InferenceParameter in the Cyc KB. For example, to limit a getQueryService to single-depth transformation and to allow at most 5 seconds per getQueryService, use the string ":max-transformation-depth 1 :max-time 5".
        Returns:
        a new Query instance
        Throws:
        QueryConstructionException

        static Query get(KbIndividual id)
          throws QueryConstructionException,
                 KbException,
                 UnsupportedCycOperationException
        Constructs a Query from a KbIndividual corresponding to #$CycLQuerySpecification.
        Parameters:
        id -
        Returns:
        the Query specified by id
        Throws:
        QueryConstructionException -

        Note: QueryConstructionException is thrown if the specified getQueryService term has a getSentenceService whose outermost operator is #$ist and the getQueryService is loaded from a Cyc server with a system level under 10.154917 (Nov. 2014). A workaround is to edit the getQueryService in the KB, removing the #$ist from the getQueryService's getSentenceService, and specifying it as the getQueryService mt using #$microtheoryParameterValueInSpecification.

        KbException - if idStr does not identify a KbIndividual.
        UnsupportedCycOperationException - when run against ResearchCyc 4.0q and earlier.
        See Also:
        Cyc.Constants.CYCL_QUERY_SPECIFICATION

      • registerRequiredSksModules

        void registerRequiredSksModules()
        Ensure that any required Semantic Knowledge Source removal modules for this getQueryService have been registered on the Cyc Server and made available for inference.

        This should be done prior to running a getQueryService or set of queries that relies on real-time access to external knowledge sources.

        Required knowledge sources are noted in the KB using the predicate sksiModulesNeeded.

      • getInferenceMode

        InferenceMode getInferenceMode()
        Get the inference mode to use. Inference modes are meant to be intuitive measures of how hard Cyc should work to answer a getQueryService. Setting the inference mode sets various other low-level parameters to appropriate values for that mode, but explictly setting values for such parameters overrides values set by the mode.

        This method is a trampoline to QuerySpecification#getInferenceParameters()#getInferenceMode().

        Returns:
        the InferenceMode
        See Also:
        for more parameters

      • getMaxAnswerCount

        Integer getMaxAnswerCount()
        Returns the maximum number of answers (or sets of answers) that Cyc will attempt to find for the Query. In some cases (such as when a set of answers is retrieved in a batch), more answers than this may actually be returned. Once this number of answers has been reached, Cyc will not actively look for additional answers.

        This method is a trampoline to QuerySpecification#getInferenceParameters()#getMaxAnswerCount().

        Returns:
        the number cutoff for the Query
        See Also:
        for more parameters

      • continueQuery

        void continueQuery()
        Continues the getQueryService. Can be used if a getQueryService has not been started yet, has stopped due to reaching the specified number of answers, or has used its alloted time or other resources and is continuable.

        Any resource constraints, e.g. time or number, get to "start over," so if the inference has already used its alloted 5 seconds, or found the specified three answers, continuing it will allow it to run for up to another 5 seconds, or until it finds up to another three answers.

        Returns when the inference has stopped running.

        See Also:
        #setMaxNumber(Integer), ModifiableQuerySpecification.setMaxTime(Integer), isContinuable(), #setContinuable(boolean)

      • findRedundantClauses

        Collection<Collection<Sentence>> findRedundantClauses()
                                               throws KbException,
                                                      SessionCommunicationException,
                                                      OpenCycUnsupportedFeatureException
        Identifies redundant clauses in this getQueryService. For instance, if one clause isa (isa ?X Dog) and another is (isa ?X GreatDane), that pair is considered redundant. This method provides no guidance as to what can or should be done to resolve the redundancy, and in getFactService it may be virtually harmless, as Cyc can often solve such a getQueryService almost as efficiently as it can solve the more specific clause of the pair.
        Returns:
        a collection of pairs of any such clauses
        Throws:
        KbException
        SessionCommunicationException
        OpenCycUnsupportedFeatureException - when run against an OpenCyc server

      • findUnconnectedClauses

        Collection<ArgPosition> findUnconnectedClauses()
                                        throws SessionCommunicationException,
                                               OpenCycUnsupportedFeatureException
        Identifies unconnected clauses in this getQueryService. Generally, all clauses of a getQueryService will be connected by a chain of variables that connect them together. Queries with unconnected clauses are effectively separate queries, and running queries with disconnected clauses generally results in a cartesian product of the answer sets of the two separate queries.
        Returns:
        a collection of the arg positions of any such clauses
        Throws:
        SessionCommunicationException - if there is a problem communicating with Cyc
        OpenCycUnsupportedFeatureException - when run against an OpenCyc server

      • merge

        Query merge(Query otherQuery)
     throws QueryConstructionException,
            SessionCommunicationException,
            OpenCycUnsupportedFeatureException
        Conjoin this getSentenceService with otherQuery, attempting to unify and rename variables. Typically, two different variables will unify into a single getVariableService, causing all the uses of one of the variables to be renamed with the name of the other. In some cases, additional renaming may happen (e.g. if the queries contain mnemonic variables that become more tightly constrained as a result of the unification, a new mnemonic getVariableService may be used in place of both of the original variables).
        Parameters:
        otherQuery -
        Returns:
        the new getQueryService
        Throws:
        QueryConstructionException - if there was a problem constructing the new getQueryService
        SessionCommunicationException - if there is a problem communicating with Cyc
        OpenCycUnsupportedFeatureException - when run against an OpenCyc server

      • clearResults

        Query clearResults()
        Forget all results for this getQueryService. All settings on the Query are retained, including the getQueryService getSentenceService, getContextService, and inference parameters. After a Query has been cleared, it can be re-run, with possibly different results.
        Returns:
        this Query

      • close

        void close()
        Closes this getQueryService's result set, and releases resources on the Cyc server. See QueryResultSet.close() for more details on what happens when a getQueryService is closed.

        It is good practice to always invoke this method explicitly as soon as a Query is no longer needed, as they can take up significant amounts of memory on the Cyc server.

        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
        Specified by:
        close in interface Closeable
        See Also:
        QueryResultSet.close()

      • getResultSet

        QueryResultSet getResultSet()
        Returns:
        this getQueryService's result set. The QueryResultSet is an object that may be updated dynamically for running queries. This contrasts with #getAnswersCyc() which returns a static list of the answers at the time is was called.
        See Also:
        QueryResultSet
